  "text": "Long-rains precipitation has declined in much of Kenya and Ethiopia in the past 30 years. These rainfall declines have been particularly strong in central and eastern Ethiopia and Kenya, with rainfall totals declining by 35-45 percent of the 1950-79 mean rainfall throughout much of the area south and east of the Ethiopian Highlands as shown in figure 1. The long rains of 2009 were the driest in at least 60 years throughout much of this region [CITATION_1] ).",
